{
  "texts": [
    "For three classes, this model averaged 96.72 percent precision, 96.69 percent accuracy, 96.84 percent recall, and 96.68 percent F1-score.A model called CoroNet [13] was created by Asif et al.",
    "They used two sources to create their dataset [14,15].",
    "They gathered 1,300 photos altogether from both of these sources.",
    "The dataset included the classes Normal, COVID-19, Bacterial Pneumonia, and Viral Pneumonia.",
    "They changed all of the photos to have a resolution of 72 dpi and a size of 224 * 224 pixels."
  ]
}